<i>adverb</i>: 하마터면 [하마터면], 얼추 [얼추], 다 [다ː], 거의 [거의/거이] <i>noun</i>: 거의 [거의/거이] <br>
<ul>
<li><i>adverb</i><br>
<dt><span>&#8227;&nbsp;</span>하마터면 [하마터면]</dt><br>
<dd>almost; barely; nearly</dd><br>
<dd>조금만 잘못했더라면.</dd><br>
<dd>If something had gone wrong even slightly.</dd><br>
<dt><span>&#8227;&nbsp;</span>얼추 [얼추]</dt><br>
<dd>1. approximately</dd><br>
<dd>어지간한 정도로 대충.</dd><br>
<dd>Quite roughly.</dd><br>
<dd>2. almost</dd><br>
<dd>어떤 기준에 거의 가깝게.</dd><br>
<dd>Nearly close to a certain standard.</dd><br>
<dt><span>&#8227;&nbsp;</span>다 [다ː]</dt><br>
<dd>1. all; everything</dd><br>
<dd>남거나 빠진 것이 없이 모두.</dd><br>
<dd>With nothing left over or missing.</dd><br>
<dd>2. almost</dd><br>
<dd>행동이나 상태의 정도가 한정된 정도에 거의 가깝게.</dd><br>
<dd>Nearly close to the limit in terms of the degree of behavior or state.</dd><br>
<dd>3. surprisingly; unexpectedly</dd><br>
<dd>가벼운 놀람, 감탄, 비꼼 등을 나타내어 ‘의외로’.</dd><br>
<dd>The word meaning 'unexpectedly' that expresses a slight surprise, admiration, sarcasm, etc.</dd><br>
<dd>4. all</dd><br>
<dd>아무런 쓸모나 좋을 것 없이.</dd><br>
<dd>Without any use or benefit.</dd><br>
<dd>5. completely</dd><br>
<dd>(반어적으로) 이룰 수 없게 된 미래의 일에 쓰여 ‘아주’, ‘완전히’.</dd><br>
<dd>(ironic) The word meaning 'very,' or 'completely' relating to some future plan that seems totally implausible.</dd><br>
<dt><span>&#8227;&nbsp;</span>거의 [거의/거이]</dt><br>
<dd>1. all but</dd><br>
<dd>전부에서 조금 모자라게.</dd><br>
<dd>A little less than all.</dd><br>
<dd>2. nearly; almost</dd><br>
<dd>어떤 상태나 한도에 매우 가깝게.</dd><br>
<dd>In the state of being very close to a state or limit.</dd><br>
</li>
<li><i>noun</i><br>
<dt><span>&#8227;&nbsp;</span>거의 [거의/거이]</dt><br>
<dd>most; almost</dd><br>
<dd>전부에서 조금 모자란 정도.</dd><br>
<dd>A little less than all.</dd><br>
</li>
</ul>